Solution: In addressing inquiries from the African-American heart failure patient regarding food, it would be beneficial to provide tailored dietary recommendations that align with her socio-economic status, cultural background, and potential barriers to adherence. Encouraging a heart-healthy diet that is rich in fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins while limiting sodium and saturated fats can help manage heart failure symptoms and improve overall health.

