Solve Barrier: To overcome this barrier, it would be helpful to engage the patient in open and non-judgmental discussions about her food preferences and cultural background, while also providing education on the importance of dietary modifications in managing heart failure. Offering practical strategies, such as gradual changes, meal planning tips, and involving family members in meal preparation, can help facilitate successful dietary modifications.

